New layouts, both here and at the almanac. And now that I've worked myself well past suppertime, I'm going to find some food before I collapse and kitties eat me.

made me do it. ;) [01] -- Go to IMDB.com and look up your 10 favorite TV shows. [02] -- Post three official IMDB "Plot Keywords" for these 10 picks. [03] -- Have your friends guess the show names. 01. character name in title :: neo noir :: dead girl Veronica Mars, 02. cliffhanger :: surreal :: escaped prisoner Lost, 03. jealousy :: alcoholism :: teen angst The O.C., 04. mustache :: karma :: maid My Name Is Earl, 05. prostitute :: profanity :: good vs. evil Deadwood, 06. wisecrack humor :: cult favourite :: female soldier 07. awkward :: pretzel :: downsizing The Office, 08. small town :: library :: resurrection Buffy the Vampire Slayer, 09. monkey :: platonic love :: coffee shop Friends, 10. self sacrifice :: brother :: murder Prison Break, (note: not all are still on the air)

(from , so blame her) 1) What TV show(s) do you find yourself watching the most? Gosh, lately? Lots of The Office, My Name Is Earl, LOST, Veronica Mars, and Prison Break, if I'm doing a most frequent top five. But Grey's Anatomy and Weeds are way up there, and I can see Heroes joining the ranks too. And of course, my daily routine always includes The Simpsons reruns and a healthy dose of The Daily Show. 2) What if any TV shows do you own on DVD? Errr... This is going to be a long list. Buffy (full series), Alias (full series), Friends (full series), Dawson's Creek (full series, and shut up), Gilmore Girls (s1-5), Angel (s1-3, 5), Office (UK, s1-2), Veronica Mars (s1), Lost (s1), The O.C. (s1-2), Survivor (s1-2, All Stars), Sopranos (s1-4), Curb Your Enthusiasm (s1-2), Deadwood (s1), My Name Is Earl (s1), Weeds (s1), C.S.I. (s1-2), Desperate Housewives (s1), Firefly (s1, -not- a full series, jerks), X-Files (s1), Simpsons (s1-4), Fishing With John (full series), The Ben Stiller Show (full series), and a handful of Twilight Zone and Alfred Hitchcock Presents "best of" discs. 3) Can you name your favorite TV show theme song (I would encourage you to make a phone post and sing it to us)? No singing. :) But I'm gonna kick it new school on this, and say the s3 Veronica Mars theme. Love that reworking of "We Used to Be Friends." 4) Have you ever been on TV and if so for what? Nosir! 5) What is your favorite YouTube video (feel free to post a link)? Okay, besides 's, I would have to say my favourite is: X & Y - Jim and Pam... It's beautifully done, from scene and music selection, to the pacing of the clips.. I love it. (so thanks to aforementioned girl for sending it, but she didn't make it so it's not cheating! :D)

Six facts about me in this sixth month in the year 2006, as requested by the lovely . 1. I dislike riding in elevators, though I am not claustrophobic. 2. There is a monkey on the couch in my basement. 3. My favourite literary character is Eddie Dean. 4. It's been over two years since I took a picture on film. 5. I have, so far, only put up four things on the walls of my new office. 6. I suspect not waiting until tomorrow to do this list of six was either a mistake, or the salvation of my eternal soul. If you tag them, they will come... , , (and yes, in keeping with the theme, technically you're supposed to tag six other people, but hell if I know that many that haven't been tagged already, so deal :P)

Guilt
What is yours?
Explain yourself
Culinary: Swedish Fish Dark chocolate is actually the candy I eat most regularly, but I'm never actually guilty about it since it's like, you know, real food. It comes from nature, if not god himself, and has those good whosiwhatsits in it that do something or another for the ol' ticker like red wine does. But Swedish Fish... I mean, I'm pretty sure there's no honest to god food in them. They're just... red. That describes both their flavor and appearance. They aren't cherry, you see. Or strawberry. Or snozberry, for that matter. They're just red. And I love them. So there.
Literary: Supernatural thrillers I've got classics collecting dust on my shelf, future classics collecting dust on my nightstand, and yet what am I really excited about? The new Kim Harrison. Don't tell my dad...
Audiovisual: The O.C. I watch a lot of tv. I mean, really. A lot. But in large part, I think a lot of it is good quality stuff. My office space proudly proclaims to perfect strangers my love of Buffy, I wear my Oceanic Airlines t-shirt with that same sense of pride, and hey, if you've got to watch reality tv, Survivor is the way to go. But The O.C.? *wince* It started out good. Those first six episodes were Quality. But from there... Well, I love it anyways, and I always will, but it definitely crossed over into a guilty pleasure a loonnng time ago.
Musical: Nothing! That's right! Nothing I listen to gives me guilt or shame. Once upon a time, I might have listed Ryan Adams, but the man's good. I can't deny it anymore. He's good, and I like him, and I don't care who knows!
Celebrity: Kate Moss I know she's a cokehead, and she sets an impossible body image for impressionable young minds, and the first time I heard her interviewed, I kind of had to cringe. But... the girl can take a picture. To put it mildly. I think she's lovely and I probably always will, and I really hope she works things out with that nice boy from Babyshambles.

This was getting too long to be in my userinfo without being irritating, so I figured I'd better jump on the resource post bandwagon. :) The custom brushes and textures distributed freely by the artists below are what turn an ordinary, 100x100 picture into a unique expression, into an icon, and I thank them heartily for making the internet a prettier place. Brushes, textures, tutorials; all completley stunning. I'm constantly amazed by the work these folks are putting out. A HUGE THANKS TO: Of course, what would I have to brush if it wasn't for loads and loads of screen captures? Screencap Paradise keeps me in Buffy caps. Striped Wall is my place for Heroes, capped by . for various. Prison Break Online gives me all of my Care Bears caps. (Oh, please. If I had to say it...) VM Caps, well, you figure it out. for Black Donnellys caps. for Friday Night Lights caps. in a dream for Freaks & Geeks (making themselves my heroes in the process, because those babies are hard to track down!) Oh Pistol Screencaps for The Tudors and finally, .. daydreaming .. keeps me well-stocked in the vast and miscellaneous "other tv" category. Making good caps is a tedious and often thankless process, as I've experienced myself in taking caps of movies, and the aforementioned sites put out beautiful caps every week. They rock, and plainly put, I couldn't do it without them. Thanks, guys, for making the rest of us look so good! Note: Credit where credit is due! Is your name missing? Comment and let me know!
